To connect ubuntu 14.04 to the vpn

  Install openvpn on local machine
    $ sudo apt-get install openvpn network-manager-openvpn network-manager-openvpn-gnome

  Download the following files from cowboyrobotics.com
    ca.crt
    client.ovpn
    "username".crt
    "username".key

  Edit the client.ovpn file
    Change "remote my-server-1 1194" to "remote cowboyrobotics.com 1194"
    Uncoment "user nobody" and "group nogroup"
    Change "ca ca.crt" to "ca /path/to/ca.crt"
    Change "cert client.crt" to "cert /path/to/your/client.crt"
    Change "key client.key" to "key /path/to/your/client.key"

  Connecting to the vpn via command line
    $ sudo openvpn --config /path/to/client.ovpn

  Connecting to vpn via networn manager
    Go to the Network Connections window
    Click Add
    Choose OpenVPN from the drop down menu and click create
    Choose a connection name
    Set the Gateway to cowboyrobotics.com
    Choose your user certificate "<your_crt>.crt"
    Choose the CA Certificate "ca.crt"
    Choose the Private Key "<your_key>.key"
    Click Save
    Click the network dropdown menue, then go to VPN Connections and click your newly created vpn connection

  To automatically connect using the command
    Add "openvpn --config /path/to/client.ovpn" to the rc.local file

  To automatically connect with the network manager
    Go to the network manager
    Click the wifi or ethernet connection you want the vpn connection to go over
    Click Edit
    Go to the General tab
    Check the "Automatically connect to VPN when using this connection" box
    Then choose the vpn connction that you previously made
    Then click save

  Lastly restart computer to check that it will automatically connect
